of his memories

00:23.540 --> 00:26.923
♪ Still echo her eyes

00:29.167 --> 00:33.481
♪ He cried like a baby

00:34.551 --> 00:37.692
♪ And he screamed
like a panther

00:37.727 --> 00:40.419
♪ In the middle of the night

00:42.870 --> 00:46.184
♪ And he saddled his pony

00:48.427 --> 00:51.672
♪ And he went for a ride

00:51.706 --> 00:55.641
MALE REPORTER:
In other news,
God is coming to Annville!

00:55.676 --> 00:58.472
Or so some local residents
seem to be saying.

00:58.506 --> 01:01.199
Why don't you come down
to the All Saints' Church
this Sunday

01:01.233 --> 01:03.649
and see for yourself
what's what?

01:03.684 --> 01:07.619
In not-unrelated news,
local freak, Eugene Root,
remains missing,

01:07.653 --> 01:11.485
and Preacher Custer
continues to be sought by
law enforcement.

01:12.279 --> 01:13.418
Hey, Mabel!

01:13.452 --> 01:14.867
[SIRENS WAILING]

01:25.050 --> 01:26.500
[INSECTS CHIRPING]

01:27.984 --> 01:29.365
[ENGINE REVS]

01:31.091 --> 01:32.368
[WIND WHISTLES]

01:34.853 --> 01:41.653
♪ I got the bo-o-o-owling
ba-a-all blues

01:41.687 --> 01:43.620
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS] ♪ When I first started bowling

01:43.655 --> 01:45.208
♪ Just a spare was great

01:45.243 --> 01:48.901
♪ And my score
looked good at 108

01:48.936 --> 01:50.627
♪ And they
said if I practiced

01:50.662 --> 01:52.595
♪ I could raise my game [BELLS JINGLE]

01:52.629 --> 01:54.044
So I practiced
and I practiced

01:54.079 --> 01:56.116
♪ But I still bowl the same

01:57.462 --> 02:02.812
♪ I got the bo-o-o-owling
ba-a-all blues ♪

02:02.846 --> 02:05.194
[MUSIC CONTINUES OVER RADIO]

02:05.228 --> 02:07.230
What the hell's
all this about?

02:07.265 --> 02:09.819
Told you on the phone.
God's coming.

02:09.853 --> 02:11.441
Come on, Mose.

02:11.476 --> 02:12.994
You don't believe
all that crap.

02:13.029 --> 02:14.858
Well, better safe
than sorry.

02:15.514 --> 02:16.584
Where is he?

02:18.966 --> 02:21.348
What happened? Root get him?

02:22.245 --> 02:24.937
[SIGHS]
Redneck son of a bitch.

02:24.972 --> 02:27.837
Uh, rumor has it
that an even worse redneck

02:27.871 --> 02:29.252
got a hold of Preacher.

02:30.322 --> 02:32.152
Son of a bitch-ier, too.

02:34.361 --> 02:36.432
[MUSIC OVER RADIO CONTINUES]

02:36.949 --> 02:38.088
Donnie.

02:45.544 --> 02:46.856
[SMACKING]

02:46.890 --> 02:48.340
[MOANING]

02:55.761 --> 02:57.349
[SIGHS]

03:04.874 --> 03:06.358
I missed you.

03:12.330 --> 03:13.641
Where is he?

03:13.676 --> 03:15.678
What? I said, where is he?

03:15.712 --> 03:16.713
He's half-deaf, bitch.

03:17.127 --> 03:18.370
[GRUNTS]

03:18.405 --> 03:19.785
Where's Jesse?

03:19.820 --> 03:20.821
[DOOR OPENS]

03:25.205 --> 03:26.585
Hey, Tulip.

03:27.621 --> 03:28.898
What are you
doing here?

03:30.520 --> 03:32.004
Door's open, idiot!

03:32.039 --> 03:33.074
Shut up.

03:33.109 --> 03:34.248
[BETSY GROANS]

03:36.216 --> 03:38.632
CASSIDY: It's like, one loo
and you're done.

03:38.666 --> 03:41.704
She's burned herself
into your brain.

03:41.738 --> 03:46.226
That face,
those eyes, that smile.

03:46.260 --> 03:48.055
MAN: For me, it's a big,
fluffy ass.

03:48.089 --> 03:49.677
[EXHALES]
Ah.

03:49.712 --> 03:52.232
Well, you know,
whatever floats your boat.

03:53.440 --> 03:54.958
All right, Larry.

03:54.993 --> 03:56.719
Prairie Dog
dropped the charges.

03:56.753 --> 03:57.961
You're good to go.

03:59.066 --> 04:00.309
Hey, listen.

04:03.622 --> 04:05.762
I know you're hurting,

04:05.797 --> 04:07.626
but maybe you and Pedro
just take a break.

04:07.661 --> 04:10.388
Leave it up on
Brokeback Mountain
for now, all right?

04:10.422 --> 04:11.630
Off you go.

04:16.117 --> 04:17.395
[KEYS RATTLE]

04:23.366 --> 04:25.610
Where is he?

04:25.644 --> 04:30.235
Like I told your guys,
I have no idea.

04:30.270 --> 04:33.134
The past few days,
me and Padrehave
been laying low,

04:33.169 --> 04:34.757
and hanging out
at the whorehouse,

04:34.791 --> 04:36.310
where you got me and...

04:36.345 --> 04:37.311
Not Custer.

04:38.864 --> 04:41.281
Come Sunday,
I know where to find him.

04:42.454 --> 04:43.628
[CLANG]

04:44.939 --> 04:47.045
I meant Eugene.

04:48.322 --> 04:49.634
What'd Preacher
do with him?

04:49.668 --> 04:51.187
Sheriff.

04:52.568 --> 04:55.709
You're going to have
to trust me on this one.

04:57.676 --> 04:58.988
You don't wanna know.

05:00.265 --> 05:01.542
Don't I, though?

05:09.688 --> 05:14.314
I see that you are
no stranger to our
criminal justice system.

05:16.730 --> 05:18.007
[SNIFFLES]

05:18.041 --> 05:19.836
CASSIDY: Uh-oh.

05:19.871 --> 05:22.114
Manila folder time.

05:22.149 --> 05:23.599
SHERIFF HUGO:
Mmm-hmm.

05:23.633 --> 05:26.360
Assault and battery
in Las Vegas.

05:26.395 --> 05:28.535
Let... Let me just say I...
Do you know what?

05:28.569 --> 05:29.950
I told them right
from the get-go,

05:29.984 --> 05:31.848
I don't... I don't like
magicians. They...

05:31.883 --> 05:34.195
Drunk and
disorderly in Denver.

05:34.230 --> 05:36.750
Lewd and lascivious
in Nashville.

05:36.784 --> 05:37.958
[LAUGHS]

05:40.409 --> 05:42.376
New York City,
attempted murder.

05:43.273 --> 05:44.620
Oh, right. I...

05:45.931 --> 05:49.072
I sort of lost my head
a bit there. Crime of passion.

05:49.763 --> 05:50.936
Judging from this,

05:50.971 --> 05:53.491
you're a very passionate man,
Mr. Cassidy.

05:54.457 --> 05:56.148
What catches
my eye though,

05:57.564 --> 06:00.808
are the dates
of your arrests.

06:02.914 --> 06:04.467
1961,

06:05.572 --> 06:06.883
1950,

06:07.953 --> 06:09.472
1940,

06:10.611 --> 06:12.164
1922.

06:12.958 --> 06:15.547
And so on
and so forth.

06:15.582 --> 06:16.928
[TOILET LID SLAMS]

06:19.102 --> 06:20.897
And yet I look
so young.

06:22.312 --> 06:24.142
[UNZIPS] Everybody says that...

06:24.176 --> 06:25.315
[URINATING] But thank you.

06:25.350 --> 06:26.351
Yeah.

06:26.696 --> 06:27.697
[SIGHS]

06:30.424 --> 06:32.046
I noticed the sunglasses.

06:34.152 --> 06:37.638
I noticed the
goofy hats.

06:40.676 --> 06:42.505
I just wrote it down
to you being an asshole.

06:42.540 --> 06:43.679
[CHUCKLES]

06:45.335 --> 06:46.923
No, Sheriff.

06:47.855 --> 06:48.960
[CLICKS TONGUE]

06:48.994 --> 06:50.686
I'm not an asshole. [ZIPS]

06:51.514 --> 06:52.653
I'm the asshole.

06:52.688 --> 06:54.206
[SCREAMS][GUNSHOT]

06:54.241 --> 06:56.864
[GRUNTING]

07:00.040 --> 07:01.110
[COUGHS]

07:01.144 --> 07:02.525
[GROANING]

07:09.083 --> 07:11.603
Now, this is
medicine for you.

07:12.811 --> 07:15.227
At least, that's what
I've read on the Internet.

07:19.784 --> 07:23.960
Come on, vampire.
It's gonna be a long night.

07:27.481 --> 07:28.965
DONNIE:
I've been washed clean.

07:30.484 --> 07:33.556
I had Preacher dead to rights
in that church.

07:33.591 --> 07:36.525
Could have killed him
and been a hero for it, too.

07:36.559 --> 07:38.147
But I stopped myself.

07:38.181 --> 07:40.701
I remembered he'd been
merciful with me before.

07:42.323 --> 07:44.705
You remember
when we was in the men's room

07:44.740 --> 07:45.810
together that night?

07:46.189 --> 07:47.467
Uh-huh.

07:47.501 --> 07:50.055
He could have
killed me that night,
but he didn't do it.

07:50.090 --> 07:51.160
Preacher was merciful.

07:52.161 --> 07:54.370
Yeah, so
I was merciful, too.

07:55.509 --> 07:57.546
So then, when I heard
he was on the run,

07:57.580 --> 07:59.893
I told him he could
hide out here.

07:59.927 --> 08:01.964
'Cause Preacher saved me.

08:05.139 --> 08:06.762
He showed me that I...

08:09.005 --> 08:10.490
I'm not a murderer.

08:11.836 --> 08:13.734
[SHAKILY] He showed me
that I'm not the bad guy.

08:15.391 --> 08:16.496
[TULIP CLEARS THROAT]

08:17.048 --> 08:19.291
And, um,

08:19.326 --> 08:24.158
he showed you
all this in a gas
station men's room, huh?

08:24.193 --> 08:25.643
Lose the
attitude, okay?

08:27.127 --> 08:30.406
It takes a real man
to let God in his heart.

08:32.408 --> 08:34.410
We're gonna go
grab a smoke, okay?

08:36.550 --> 08:40.278
I come back to the
whole town going crazy
over God showing up.

08:40.312 --> 08:41.728
And now Donnie Schenck

08:41.762 --> 08:44.282
drooling and acting like
you're the Dalai Lama?

08:44.316 --> 08:46.180
What the hell's
going on, Jesse?

08:46.215 --> 08:47.734
I'll bring you
up to speed.

08:48.907 --> 08:52.117
First, you came
back for me.

08:53.360 --> 08:56.570
Yeah, well, after
that phone message,
how could I resist?

08:56.605 --> 08:59.366
[DEEP VOICE] "Hi, Tulip, uh,
I... I just ate pancakes."

09:02.472 --> 09:03.784
[SIGHS]

09:05.993 --> 09:07.339
I'm sorry, Tulip.

09:17.004 --> 09:18.109
You should be.

09:24.115 --> 09:25.530
Do something
for me, Jesse?

09:25.565 --> 09:26.566
Anything.

09:28.153 --> 09:29.361
Yeah?

09:30.639 --> 09:32.157
'Cause, um...

09:33.676 --> 09:37.162
I mean, it's bad.
Like, really bad.

09:37.197 --> 09:39.958
Mmm. I mean, nasty.

09:41.304 --> 09:43.134
[LAUGHS] Mmm-hmm.

09:45.861 --> 09:48.173
Anything, right? Whatever you want.

09:48.691 --> 09:50.003
[UNLOCKS TRUNK]

09:54.110 --> 09:55.353
Kill him.

09:58.321 --> 09:59.633
Well, I had to step
to him and say,

09:59.668 --> 10:02.981
"Listen, my ma
drives me crazy
sometimes, too,

10:03.016 --> 10:04.776
"but that's
your madre,brah.

10:04.811 --> 10:07.779
"You gotta respect her
like you gots to
respect all women."

10:07.814 --> 10:10.023
It's so nice
to hear a man talk like that.

10:10.057 --> 10:12.508
I mean, I'm not...
I'm not trying to be like...

10:12.542 --> 10:16.616
I'm just saying,
in the end, you,
me, our moms,

10:18.100 --> 10:19.688
we're all
just people.

10:21.793 --> 10:23.553
Well, I'd better
get back to work.

10:23.588 --> 10:25.590
Yeah, yeah, me, too.

10:25.625 --> 10:29.214
You know, uh,
I'll bring those
in for you.

10:29.249 --> 10:32.286
Okay. Thanks, Carlos. Yeah.

10:34.910 --> 10:36.083
Hey, Jennifer.

10:38.499 --> 10:39.984
You like
Chinese food?

10:42.193 --> 10:43.884
Not really.

10:46.197 --> 10:47.405
Puta.

10:53.480 --> 10:55.240
[SIGHS]

10:55.275 --> 10:57.346
JESSE: We like Chinese food.

10:57.380 --> 10:58.865
[LAUGHTER]

11:00.245 --> 11:02.592
Yeah, yeah, laugh it up.

11:04.905 --> 11:06.113
What's up?

11:07.287 --> 11:08.771
Poor Carlos.

11:08.806 --> 11:10.946
Poor Carlos.

11:10.980 --> 11:12.602
Chinese food would
be good, though.

11:12.637 --> 11:15.605
Yep. And a nice cold beer.

11:15.640 --> 11:17.815
Un-huh.
You can't have beer. Says who?

11:17.849 --> 11:19.471
If I'm not havin' beer,
neither are you.

11:19.506 --> 11:22.095
All right. Whisky it is.

11:22.923 --> 11:23.993
Asswipe.

11:27.203 --> 11:29.343
Oh, my God. [CLATTERS]

11:29.378 --> 11:30.448
What?

11:30.482 --> 11:32.519
No, no, no, no,
no, no, no, no.

11:32.553 --> 11:35.695
What is it, Jesse? Show me.

11:36.834 --> 11:38.283
I'll show you.

11:42.425 --> 11:44.220
I'll show you big time.

11:46.015 --> 11:49.225
What the... No.

11:49.260 --> 11:51.400
Oh, yeah. That is... That's wrong.

11:52.159 --> 11:53.264
Uh-huh.

11:53.298 --> 11:55.128
Come on.
It's like Lady and the Tramp,

11:55.162 --> 11:56.577
except with our butts. Jesse Custer, do not come

11:56.612 --> 11:58.890
near me with that thing,
I swear to God. [LAUGHS]

11:58.925 --> 12:01.928
Come on, you know you want it.
You know, come on.

12:01.962 --> 12:03.550
Put it away!

12:03.584 --> 12:06.001
JESSE: [CHUCKLES] Come on,
just the tip. Come on. Real professional, you two.

12:07.623 --> 12:09.763
Give us a break. Hey, Carlos.

12:09.798 --> 12:11.178
[CHUCKLES]I mean...

12:11.213 --> 12:12.732
"We are just people."

12:12.766 --> 12:14.147
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

12:14.181 --> 12:15.286
Real smooth, Carlos.

12:15.320 --> 12:17.737
Bite me.
How long to the vault?

12:18.565 --> 12:21.913
I'd say eight,
nine minutes.

12:22.569 --> 12:24.122
[BAGS ZIPPING]

12:24.157 --> 12:25.710
These are ready to go.

12:31.129 --> 12:32.786
Fun's over, Custer.

12:33.580 --> 12:35.271
Now the pain begins.

12:46.179 --> 12:47.559
[KEYS JINGLE]

12:49.492 --> 12:50.666
[SPLASH]

12:56.776 --> 12:58.639
Aw, come on.

12:59.917 --> 13:00.987
[SQUISH]

13:01.021 --> 13:01.988
[SIGHS]

13:05.715 --> 13:06.855
[SIGHS]

13:12.895 --> 13:14.000
[SIGHS]

13:17.175 --> 13:19.488
[TULIP LAUGHS]

13:19.522 --> 13:22.871
Come here,
let Mr. Fisty make
it all better.

13:22.905 --> 13:25.977
Hey, where are you going? MAN: Away from you,
you psycho.

13:26.012 --> 13:30.740
TULIP: Aw, don't run
away from Mr. Fisty.
That makes Mr. Fisty sad.

13:38.024 --> 13:40.129
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATION]

13:41.268 --> 13:42.718
[MUFFLED GROANS]

13:45.376 --> 13:48.206
MAN:
Get it away from me.

13:48.241 --> 13:49.967
TULIP: I tell you what,
let me make it up to you.

13:50.001 --> 13:51.347
MAN: I said quit it.

13:53.315 --> 13:55.041
[MUFFLED GROANING]

13:59.804 --> 14:01.530
CARLOS: Let's see if there's
Chinese food in prison.

14:11.609 --> 14:14.129
[GUNSHOT]

14:14.163 --> 14:15.716
[ALARM BLARING]

14:17.166 --> 14:19.099
[TIRES SCREECHING]

14:19.134 --> 14:20.687
No!

14:23.690 --> 14:24.933
[GASPING]

14:26.348 --> 14:28.453
Tulip, what is it?

14:28.488 --> 14:30.283
[PANTING]

14:30.317 --> 14:33.562
The baby. The baby.

14:33.596 --> 14:36.289
[SIRENS WAILING] [ALARM CONTINUES BLARING]

14:43.986 --> 14:45.125
[GRUNTS]

14:47.714 --> 14:48.922
Why?

14:48.957 --> 14:50.717
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

14:51.200 --> 14:52.684
[GRUNTS]

14:53.375 --> 14:54.479
Why?

14:56.378 --> 14:57.793
You were happy.

15:00.140 --> 15:01.314
I...

15:03.350 --> 15:05.525
[BREATHING SHAKILY]

15:12.601 --> 15:14.844
[MUSIC PLAYING]

15:19.884 --> 15:23.163
♪ Honey, won't you listen,
why don't you... ♪

15:23.198 --> 15:25.959
MAN:
French Vanilla, I remember.

15:25.994 --> 15:27.754
I don't need
to write it down

15:27.788 --> 15:29.238
'cause it's been
your blessed favorite

15:29.273 --> 15:32.345
in all the 39 years
we've been married.

15:32.379 --> 15:35.210
But, uh, maybe after
your bubble bath

15:35.244 --> 15:37.867
we could
get a little frisky.

15:38.868 --> 15:41.733
No, I didn't say dirty,
I said frisky.

15:41.768 --> 15:44.426
You know, like that time
that you wore that...

15:44.460 --> 15:48.016
No, all right, okay.
Never mind.

15:49.396 --> 15:51.329
Uh, it... It was
just a thought.

15:53.953 --> 15:55.920
Uh, hush now,

15:55.955 --> 15:58.302
no, I'm happy
no matter what we do.

15:58.336 --> 15:59.924
As long as
it's together.

16:01.581 --> 16:03.514
Yeah, a movie
sounds great.

16:04.308 --> 16:06.172
Okay. Yeah.

16:06.206 --> 16:08.553
I can see
you there. Yeah.

16:08.588 --> 16:10.003
[BUBBLING]

16:11.280 --> 16:12.488
[GRUNTING]

16:13.282 --> 16:14.490
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

16:15.250 --> 16:16.423
[GRUNTS]

16:16.458 --> 16:17.735
[BULLET CLATTERS]

16:20.738 --> 16:21.842
[PAPER CUP CRINKLES]

16:21.877 --> 16:22.947
[SIGHS]

16:22.982 --> 16:24.776
You're about
a tough son of a bitch.

16:24.811 --> 16:26.502
Well, you get used to it.

16:27.262 --> 16:28.297
Thanks.

16:30.299 --> 16:31.611
[BULLET CLATTERS]

16:34.407 --> 16:35.995
Where's Eugene?

16:38.342 --> 16:41.897
Okay, all right,
I... I can tell you this.

16:41.931 --> 16:44.003
The good news
is he's alive.

16:45.383 --> 16:47.627
Well, maybe.

16:47.661 --> 16:50.457
Mind you, that may
also be the bad news
as well, you know.

16:53.840 --> 16:54.979
Honestly,
it was an accident.

16:55.014 --> 16:57.016
You know, Jesse,
he wouldn't hurt a kid.

16:57.050 --> 16:58.362
Not on purpose,
he wouldn't.

16:58.396 --> 17:00.329
Oh, high praise, indeed.

17:02.435 --> 17:04.092
[GUN CLICKS]

17:04.126 --> 17:06.577
This world...

17:06.611 --> 17:12.169
Vampires, government agents,
psychopathic preachers.

17:12.203 --> 17:15.931
It's all
an unmitigated monster swamp.

17:15.965 --> 17:18.037
That's true.

17:18.071 --> 17:21.419
Plonkers and gobshites
as far as the eye can see.

17:21.454 --> 17:23.456
[SNIFFS]

17:23.490 --> 17:25.734
Still, nobody's perfect.
You know?

17:26.769 --> 17:28.495
I mean,
you know, [LAUGHS]

17:28.530 --> 17:30.325
I'm a dark-hearted
piece of shite.

17:31.878 --> 17:34.846
That's true.
The manila folder never lies.

17:34.881 --> 17:37.918
But what
about you, Sheriff?

17:39.196 --> 17:41.094
All this.

17:41.129 --> 17:43.683
Last I checked, this kind
of questioning was illegal.

17:43.717 --> 17:45.167
Not in Texas. [GUN COCKS]

17:46.893 --> 17:49.309
Not when a man's
looking for his son.

17:49.344 --> 17:51.139
But are you really
looking for him though,

17:51.725 --> 17:53.210
is what I'm wondering.

17:55.039 --> 17:57.559
Just, come on,
be honest with me now, like,

17:57.593 --> 18:02.391
would there not be,
like, a teeny-tiny
part of you

18:02.426 --> 18:04.704
that'd be happy
if he was just gone?

18:06.947 --> 18:09.985
Eugene's a good boy. I know, I know that.

18:10.019 --> 18:12.332
But he's sort of
annoyingly good though.

18:13.230 --> 18:14.610
Am I right?

18:14.645 --> 18:17.441
Always talking.
Asking his bloody questions.

18:17.475 --> 18:19.167
And that face.
I just...

18:21.790 --> 18:24.206
I honestly...
I don't know how you do it.

